window.docContents[51].resolve({"/p-adic-and-Adic-Spaces/Tate-algebras-and-the-structure-sheaf/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--p-adic-and-Adic-Spaces--Tate-algebras-and-the-structure-sheaf--The-structure-sheaf-on-strongly-noetherian-Tate-rings":{"contents":"(Wedhorn Theorem 8.28(b).) Let  be a strongly noetherian Tate ring\n() — one for which all Tate algebras \n() are noetherian — that is complete. Then the structure presheaf\n on  (), with\n on rational subsets (), is a\nsheaf, i.e.  is sheafy.\nFormalised in Adic-Spaces: isSheafy_of_stronglyNoetherian_828b — in progress: the gluing condition (lemma_8_34_gluing) and the algebraic separation (cor_8_32_productRestrictionSub_injective) are established, but the topological inducing half of the embedding (cor_8_32_productRestrictionSub_isInducing) still carries a sorry.\n\nIn Lean,  is the pair of an embedding condition and a gluing condition on\nevery rational covering. The proof follows Wedhorn §8 top-down.Separation and the embedding. By Corollary 8.32, the restriction map\n over a rational covering is faithfully flat, hence\ninjective (cor_8_32_productRestrictionSub_injective); the topological strengthening to an\nembedding additionally needs that this injection is inducing, the input from the Banach open-mapping\ntheorem (BanachOMT) — this last inducing step is the remaining sorry. Faithful flatness comes from\nLemma 8.31: the Tate algebra  is faithfully flat over  and the quotients\n,  are flat (), using\nthe strongly noetherian hypothesis to identify  (Examples 6.38/6.39).Gluing. For compatible sections over a rational cover, a global section is produced by Tate\nacyclicity (lemma_8_34_gluing): the two-element Laurent cover  gives the exact\nsequence\n\n(), Lemma 8.33; Wedhorn's refinement (Prop A.3) lifts acyclicity from Laurent\ncovers to all rational covers, and Prop A.4 packages acyclicity into the sheaf property.\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009p-adic and Adic Spaces\u0009Tate algebras and the structure sheaf","header":"5.13.2. The structure sheaf on strongly noetherian Tate rings","id":"/p-adic-and-Adic-Spaces/Tate-algebras-and-the-structure-sheaf/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--p-adic-and-Adic-Spaces--Tate-algebras-and-the-structure-sheaf--The-structure-sheaf-on-strongly-noetherian-Tate-rings"}});